Florence FFA
2 hrs ·

Meet your 2020-2021 Florence FFA
Treasurer, Tyler Edgar. This is not Tyler's first rodeo, last year he also served as the Florence FFA Treasurer. He competes in an abundance of events in the FFA such as Milk Quality and Food Science. Tyler is an asset to the officer team because of his generous personality, and ability to pick up and handle whatever is thrown at him. Tyler is a smart, skilled leader for this team. His advice to younger FFA members is to be involved and be dedicated to managing your time to do as many things as possible. Hard work will pay off in the Florence FFA. Tyler looks forward to an exciting senior year to help motivate members to be more active in the program.

Florence FFA
September 9 at 12:49 PM ·

Meet your 2020-2021 Florence FFA President, Kailee Hilton. Kailee Is a senior this year and has recently served as the Florence FFA Vice President, and Cen-Tex District Vice President. She is involved in an abundance of activities including Meat Judging, Wool Judging, Public Speaking, Science Fair, Public Relations, Showing Livestock and much more. Kailee has traveled to both the State and National Convention to compete in contests and has succeeded in bringing home banners. Her advice to younger members is to never give up and always keep in mind that everything happens for a reason. She encourages people to believe that god has a plan for everything. Kailee looks forward to serving the chapter that has molded her into the person she is today.

post_text: Florence ISD will be distributing Chromebook devices to Remote learners only this Thursday, August 27, 2020, at the Florence Elementary Cafeteria. We have two deployment times. The second deployment will start at 2:00 p.m. and run until 3:30 p.m. Please come to receive the Chromebook device in the parking lot in front of the Florence Elementary cafeteria. We ask that you DO NOT get out of your car. If you are unable to pick up a device on August 27th, you will need to pick up the device on Friday, August 28, 2020, from 9:00 a.m. - 11:00 a.m. at the same location.

Parents,
Due to the adjustment of the school start date, instructional choice settings (either remote or in-person) will need to be completed by noon on Friday, August 21, 2020, so that students’ schedules can be finalized. If no selection is made by this date, the student will automatically default to the in-person option. The choice form is located on the district website and Facebook page. Be sure to read the "FISD Plan for a Strong Start to the 2020-2021 School Year" to learn more about each option prior to making your selection.
If you have already completed the instructional setting choice form, please disregard this message.

post_text:
Due to circumstances beyond our control, Florence ISD will delay the first day of instruction for the 2020-2021 School Year to August 31, 2020.

Our teachers, administrators, and staff have worked tirelessly to prepare for the start of school during this difficult and challenging time. However, a number of obstacles currently exist. These obstacles can be overcome with this additional time.

FISD students deserve the best opportunity for success that we can provide. In order for that to happen, our faculty and staff must have the time to fully prepare. This will give us the opportunity to provide the strong start we all desire.

Additional detailed information regarding instruction and the start of school will be forthcoming from your child’s campus administrators and teachers.

We appreciate your understanding and patience and trust that you know our primary concern is your child’s well-being and success.

Florence FFA
July 6 at 10:08 AM ·

Help us welcome our new Ag Science Teacher to the Florence FFA family!

Mrs. Smith grew up in LaPlata New Mexico, where she was an active member of 4-H and FFA, showed pigs and goats, and competed in livestock and meat judging. After high school, she attended college at South Plains College in Levelland, TX on a livestock judging scholarship. Following SPC, she went on to Texas Tech University, where she was a member of the 2015 National Champion Meat Judging Team. In 2016, she graduated with a Bachelor's degree in Animal and Meat science. Upon graduation, she took a job with Food Safety Net Services, and has been working in the Food science industry ever since.

In 2017 she married Van Smith. They have one dog, a blue heeler named Kota. Mr. and Mrs. Smith are excited to be a part of the Florence community, and Mrs. Smith is excited to meet her students, and share her passion of Agriculture. 💙💛💜

Texas Department of Agriculture
June 22 at 1:45 PM ·

Did your child receive free or reduced-price school meals through the National School Lunch Program during the 2019-2020 school year? If so, your family may be eligible for P-EBT benefits to buy food. Eligible families should have received the application link from their school. Eligible families that received SNAP benefits for March have already received P-EBT benefits and do not have to apply. If you did not receive an application link or if you need help filling out the P-EBT application, please contact the P-EBT Call Center at 833-613-6220 Monday through Friday, 8:00 am – 6:00 pm. The deadline to apply for P-EBT is June 30, 2020. For more information, please visit http://hhs.texas.gov/pebt.

Purple & White Scholarship Recipients 2019-2020
The Purple and White Scholarship fund is supported by voluntary payroll deductions from Florence ISD staff, faculty members, and administration and by contributions from community members and local businesses. The purpose of the scholarship is to provide assistance to Florence High School graduating seniors in meeting the expenses of a college or trade school education. This year, a grand total of $12,500 is being distributed to the following students who applied for and were selected as recipients of the Purple and White Scholarship.

At the $1000 Level:
Hannah Gray
Shane Hilton
Justice Swick
Michelle Washington

At the $2000 Level:
Christian Broekhuizen
Amy Garcia
Mikaela Loerwald

At the $2500 level:
Abigail Ramirez

Congratulations to these deserving seniors!
text:
Purple & White Scholarship Recipients 2019-2020
The Purple and White Scholarship fund is supported by voluntary payroll deductions from Florence ISD staff, faculty members, and administration and by contributions from community members and local businesses. The purpose of the scholarship is to provide assistance to Florence High School graduating seniors in meeting the expenses of a college or trade school education. This year, a grand total of $12,500 is being distributed to the following students who applied for and were selected as recipients of the Purple and White Scholarship.

At the $1000 Level:
Hannah Gray
Shane Hilton
Justice Swick
Michelle Washington

At the $2000 Level:
Christian Broekhuizen
Amy Garcia
Mikaela Loerwald

At the $2500 level:
Abigail Ramirez

Congratulations to these deserving seniors!

post_text:
Graduation Announcement for Seniors and Parents:

After research and analysis of our stadium capacity and social distancing guidelines currently in place through The Texas Education Agency, we are pleased to announce that each senior will receive six tickets to the Florence High School Graduation for the Class of 2020 at Stampede Stadium on Friday, June 19, 2020 at 8:00 pm. The graduation tickets and detailed guidance will be mailed to seniors and their families on Friday, June 6, 2020. The additional guidance will include information on parking, entry and exit to the event, seating instructions, and a special surprise for our senior parents. The information will be shared via Facebook and the FHS website on Monday, June 8, 2020 after 4:00 pm. Additionally, we are pleased to announce that the Graduation ceremony will be live streamed so that we can share this moment with everyone that could not be in attendance in person.
text:

After research and analysis of our stadium capacity and social distancing guidelines currently in place through The Texas Education Agency, we are pleased to announce that each senior will receive six tickets to the Florence High School Graduation for the Class of 2020 at Stampede Stadium on Friday, June 19, 2020 at 8:00 pm. The graduation tickets and detailed guidance will be mailed to seniors and their families on Friday, June 6, 2020. The additional guidance will include information on parking, entry and exit to the event, seating instructions, and a special surprise for our senior parents. The information will be shared via Facebook and the FHS website on Monday, June 8, 2020 after 4:00 pm. Additionally, we are pleased to announce that the Graduation ceremony will be live streamed so that we can share this moment with everyone that could not be in attendance in person.

FISD Board Changes

New Board members Anthony DeAugustineo and David Edgar took the Oath of Office for service on the Florence ISD Board of Trustees along with returning board member Jeff Stone at the May Regular Meeting.
As is done annually, the board officers were elected with Ed Navarette continuing to serve as President, J.T. Atkinson will now serve as Vice-president and Jason Earp will continue as Secretary.
FISD appreciates all of our board member’s willingness to serve and looks forward to continued strong leadership and success in the future.
text:
FISD Board Changes

New Board members Anthony DeAugustineo and David Edgar took the Oath of Office for service on the Florence ISD Board of Trustees along with returning board member Jeff Stone at the May Regular Meeting.
As is done annually, the board officers were elected with Ed Navarette continuing to serve as President, J.T. Atkinson will now serve as Vice-president and Jason Earp will continue as Secretary.
FISD appreciates all of our board member’s willingness to serve and looks forward to continued strong leadership and success in the future.

post_text:
Two Longtime Board Members Honored

The FISD Board of Trustees honored two long serving members at the May meeting. Dena Shelton and Craig Clark have retired from service on the Board.
Mr. Clark earlier retired from service, but stepped up to fill a vacancy on the Board. He has approximately 20 years of service including many years as president. Anthony DeAugustineo filled Mr. Clark’s position on the Board.
Dena Shelton has served twelve years as a board member, many of those years as vice-president. Mrs. Shelton also served numerous terms as the FISD Delegate to the TASB (Texas Association of School Boards) Assembly. David Edgar filled Mrs. Shelton’s position on the Board.
These Board Members have served honorably for many years and between them, there is a wealth of knowledge and experience.
Superintendent Michalewicz presented each of them with a canvas of a Buffalo and a Challenge Coin as a token of our appreciation. The remainder of the board members each expressed their gratitude to them for their faithful service and leadership.

post_text: Beginning in June we will be going to once per week distribution. We will deliver to the bus stops 7 days' worth of food each Thursday. There will no longer be a drive-up option. We will be delivering a combination of meals and "bulk" foods. Buses will roll earlier than they are now so we can beat the heat. If you are already receiving meals by bus you are all set. If you need to be added to a route please email lragsdale@florenceisd.net with your address and number of children. Please make it a priority to be at your stop so we can prepare accurate amounts of food with our limited resources. If you miss two drops you will be taken off the route and have to sign up again. CHILDREN MUST BE PRESENT TO RECEIVE A MEAL. This institution is an equal opportunity provider.

Lunch and Breakfast selections will include turkey sandwiches(made with Jenni-O turkey and H.E.B bakery bread), cheeseburgers, whole muscle meat whole-grain chicken nuggets, pizza, spaghetti, Whole Grain muffins, kolaches, scrambled eggs, oatmeal and more....we are providing meals for 7 days per week. Notice About Ongoing Graduation Planning

We wanted to let our seniors and their parents know that graduation planning is currently underway. We are committed to developing a plan that honors our seniors and allows families to celebrate this landmark accomplishment. No decisions have been reached regarding a final plan, dates, or other details. However, rest assured that we will develop the most appropriate plan based on TEA guidance, and the guidance of state and local officials in regards to social distancing protocols.

post_text: Florence ISD will be distributing school devices on Thursday, April 23, for families with students in grades Pre-K through 12th grade that need a device. This distribution is for families that did not receive a device during our first distribution. As a reminder; these devices are for families who do not have a device at home but have an internet connection. We will distribute one device per family in need. Parents will sign a technology agreement at the time of distribution. Parents are required to be present. Please refer to the Technology Device Loan Agreement on the Florence ISD website located on the COVID 19 page. Device pickup will occur from 6:00 P.M. to 7:00 P.M. on the side of the elementary cafeteria located on N. Love Ave. At this time we will only be handing out computer/tablet devices, not internet hotspots. Internet hotspots will be delivered at a later date to families that need them. We will notify parents once we receive hotspots. Again, this is for families that have internet connectivity but do not have a device.

Note from Dr. Tarlton -

Due to the Covid-19 Virus, we will be unable to participate in the Pet Clinic in the Florence schools and others.

We are holding clinics at the following locations:
April 4
Hill Co. Feed Store in Leander this Sat. from 8:30 – 10am
and
Georgetown at Tx. Outdoor Equip on Hwy 29 way out past Cimarron Hills Subdivision from 10:30 - 12.
April 15
Georgetown Clinic from 5 - 7 pm. GT 2201 S. Austin Ave.

If you tell us you got the shots at one of the pet clinics, we can honor those prices in our office this year. We will also need to find out which pet clinic you came from and will put that school on the reminder cards for next year.

We want everyone to pre-register, if you can, so we can distance, wait in cars etc. and it will go very fast. Email LonghornLana@aol.com to pre-register.

post_text: In our continued effort to meet the needs of our students, Florence ISD has launched an all-out effort to feed the Buffs. In the very first week, we have fed 700 kids and handed out almost 10,000 meals. Organized by our Child Nutrition Director, Lillian Barnett, this is an amazing team effort by not only our dedicated food service staff, but also by administrators, transportation, and many others throughout the district. Go Buffs!

Dear Florence ISD and Community,

In an effort to limit the spread of coronavirus/COVID-19, Florence ISD will suspend normal operations for two weeks following spring break. Effectively, this will close campus operations through April 3. We will have more detailed information available soon regarding next steps for learning and business continuity. An email has been sent to all Florence ISD staff with guidance. FISD staff should check email on a daily basis.

Paul Michalewicz
Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
The Florence Athletic Department has closely monitored current information and current press releases from the UIL regarding Coronavirus (COVID19). The UIL has regulated that no athletic contests will be allowed from Monday, March 16 through Sunday, March 29. Practices are still allowed by the UIL and will continue as originally planned by each sport. This includes continuing our practice schedules during spring break.

This is a fluid situation that is experiencing high amounts of change. Any additional changes will be communicated through our district website, Facebook page, and Athletics' messaging systems. To join the Athletics' Remind messaging system text the message @florenceat to the number 81010.

We appreciate your support and want to remind everyone that the safety of our students and staff is our highest priority.

Drew Bridges
Athletic Director
Florence ISD

Florence FFA
February 27 at 4:19 PM ·

Congrats to our teams in Jacksboro today!

The Milk Quality team was 1st place! Tyler Edgar was 1st high individual, Abbie Regier placed 3rd high, John Conner was 12th high individual and Emily Gann was 15th high! Other team members include; Emerson Hawkins, Danni Hilton, Yarely Perez and Kaitlyn Cosper!

The Wildlife team was 2nd place team and Matt Toutant was 1st high individual and Justice Swick was 10th high individual! Other team members were Beau Gilmore, Tyler Simpson, Ryland Carlile, Brady Barnes, Noah Campbell, and Armondo Garcia.

The Vet Science team placed 10th overall! Kyle Earp was 11th high individual and joining him were Kendra Vaughan and Madilyn Cavender.

The Floriculture team members Abigail Brown and Taylor Cosper put up their highest scores today!

The Land team placed 9th overall! This team consisted of Christian Broekhuizen who was 17th high individual, Reese Gilmore, JR Castillo, Roy Carlson, and Clayton Brown!

We are very proud of how they represented us today! Congratulations to all our students and their hard work!

Have you seen all the slick new tools associated with our new menu software? We are now ADA compliant. Menus can be translated into tons of languages. You can track carbs, calories or any other nutrients through the "build a meal" feature. Most items have photos associated with them. Now you can click an item and a picture will pop up (most items). This is really helpful for the little bitty Buffs. Our favorite feature is the allergy filter. Just select an allergy and the software will strike out all foods containing the allergen. Just look for the three lines up at the top once you access the menu that you need.

post_text:
Today several FHS faculty/staff members (Mr. Elder, Mrs. Crow, Dr. Willingham, Coach Lewis and Ms. Nordman) took students from the FHS Practicum in Ag class to tour the Gault Site and discuss ideas for informative videos that the class will be producing on behalf of the Gault Site. A meeting was held earlier this month with archaeologists to discuss ways that FHS students and staff can form a collaborative partnership with the Gault Site and this trip was a followup to that meeting.

The Gault Site is an important and significant find for archaeologists working in Texas and across the New World. Clovis technology is 13,000 years old and has long been associated with the earliest peoples in the New World. New evidence of an earlier occupation at the Gault Site demonstrates that people were living in the Florence area 16,000 years ago, significantly increasing the age of humans in the New World.

Bond Projects Update

There will be a community-wide meeting Thursday, January 16, 2020 to provide a thorough update regarding the FISD Bond Projects. This meeting will take place in the Florence High School Library located at 401 FM 970 beginning at 6:30 p.m.

Superintendent Paul Michalewicz, along with representatives of the architectural firm Huckabee and Associates and the general contractor, Braun and Butler will present this information to the public. There will be an opportunity for attendees to ask questions.

All community members interested in this information are encouraged to attend.

post_text: Florence High School is well on its way to reaching their goal of 2,500 cans! Today was collection day for the Thanksgiving baskets - everything brought in after today through December 6th will go towards Christmas baskets. The office aides operated a collection station during homeroom and collected, counted and tallied can totals per homeroom class. Then some office aides and Dr. Willingham's class sorted all the cans by food type. As of today, 1,755 cans have been donated at FHS! If your student has not donated their 10 cans yet, they still have the opportunity to help us reach our school goal through the December 6th deadline! Go Buffs!

post_text: Attention FHS students and parents! Don't forget to bring cans for our canned food drive! Our goal as a school is 2,500 cans, and if we reach that goal, every student who brought at least 10 cans will get one day of Off Campus Lunch! The tutorial class that brings the most cans will also get a home-cooked meal provided by FHS faculty and staff! Please help us to reach or exceed our goal - start sending canned foods in now!

post_text:
11/4 High School VOTS Announcements:
Last week 7 students competed at the 91st National FFA Convention in Indianapolis Indiana. Beau Gilmore and Macey Hilton Competed with an Agriscience fair. They were a gold team and earned 2nd place. Emily Gann also competed with an agriscience fair, she was also a gold individual and earned 3rd place. Mikaela Loerwald, Kailee Hilton, Kyle Earp, and Tyler Edgar competed in the Food Science and Technology CDE.
They were a gold team and placed 5th in the nation, Kyle was 5th high individual and had the highest test score out of 150 individuals. These students brought home the gold! and did not fail in representing the Florence FFA well this past week!

On this day in History Cody Anderson and Derek Labounty were born, let's be sure to wish these boys a very special 18th Birthday!

Today for lunch is burrito con queso, chef salad, or a ham and cheese sandwich with beans and a salad bar

post_text:
Substitute Teacher Orientation and Training
Thursday, November 7, 2019 9:00 – 11:00 a.m.
Location: Florence ISD Professional Development Room,
306 College Avenue,
Florence, TX, 76527
Florence ISD is conducting substitute teacher orientation and training on Thursday, November 7, 2019, from 9:00 a.m. – 11:00 a.m. Attendance at one training and orientation session is required in order to substitute teach in Florence ISD. Attendees will not be paid for the substitute teacher training; however, the training is required annually to substitute teach in Florence ISD. The training substitute teachers receive will include
information needed to learn about substitute teaching roles and responsibilities, campus processes and procedures, and district and campus information. Florence ISD may add additional training dates to accommodate the needs of the district.
Please contact Amy Branton in Human Resources at 254-793-2850 to make application for substitute teaching in Florence ISD. Applications will also be available at the substitute teacher orientation and training.

post_text:
The October Teacher of the Month is FMS math teacher Chris Beliveau. According to Mrs. Beckerley, “Mr. B, as students refer to him, is fantastic at making math understandable. Mr. B enjoys teaching math and his dedication and energy for the subject shows when visiting his classes. Even the most resistant students enjoy Mr. B's class. One of our female students who struggles with math and is resistant to learning told me he is her favorite teacher this year because he knows how to explain math and help her to learn. With that, I happily nominate Chris Beliveau for this award.”
Mr. Beliveau will receive a $250 gift from the Florence ISD Education Foundation to be used for classroom supplies.
Congratulations Mr. Beliveau!
